defaultDFID is not default“defaultat the tabledefault”default, when it comes to disability and development. default defaultWhile DFID was a pioneer of the “twin track” strategy for disability and development, and has funded innovative projects led by disabled people and their organisatio
defaultns in the past, visibility of DFID in disability and development is now very low.  Looking at the DFID website, disability is almost invisible as an issue, and has been for some years.  As an international civil servant, I would attend meetings at UN or in
default member states, and because I am British, would be asked “Where is DFID?”:  AusAid, USAID, CIDA, Noraid, Irish Aid, JICA would be represented at these gatherings, but not DFID.
