defaultIn  the field of health, evidence suggests that approximately 10% of mothers will have some form of impairment or life limiting illness: ensuring that they are included in maternal heal
defaultth promotion efforts is vital.  Children with disabilities face higher mortality, may lose out on nutrition, may be excluded from immunisation, and may in some cases be left to die.
