default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultListening to disabled people and their organidefaultsations is vdefaultery importantdefault.
default  However, I worry that
default 
defaultsome disabled people’s organisations seem not to be very representative of the diversity of disabled people in the world, and their different viewpoints.  I find this particularly the case with some LMIC DP
defaultOs, which can be dominated by a male metropolitan middle class elite. DFID should engage with the diversity of the disability community, both domestically and on a global scale.
default  For example, people who become disabled as part of the ageing process are muc
defaulth less visible than people with congenital or traumat-related impairment.
